<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1324,975,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName box="[264,510,976,1001]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Argyrotaenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrana">
<emphasis box="[264,510,976,1001]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Argyrotaenia citrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known as the orange tortrix or apple skinworm in the older American economic literature. It occurs along the West Coast of North 
<collectingCountry box="[1029,1130,1014,1040]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">America</collectingCountry>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1202,1290,1014,1040]" name="Canada" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Canada</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[264,357,1052,1078]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. We have examined specimens from British 
<collectingCountry box="[880,999,1052,1078]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Columbia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1011,1103,1052,1078]" name="Canada" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Canada</collectingCountry>
; Washington, Oregon, California, 
<collectingCountry box="[467,551,1090,1116]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">U.S.A.</collectingCountry>
; and Baja California, 
<collectingCountry box="[830,923,1090,1116]" name="Mexico" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Mexico</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Freeman" box="[940,1133,1090,1116]" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Freeman, T. N. (1944) A review of the North American species of the genus Argyrotaenia Stephens (Lepidoptera, Tortricidae). Science and Agriculture, 25, 81 - 94." type="journal article" year="1944">
Freeman (
<number box="[1064,1125,1090,1116]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1944.0">1944</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Obraztsov" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Obraztsov, N. S. (1961) Descriptions of and notes on North and Central American species of Argyrotaenia, with description of a new genus (Lepidoptera, Tortricidae). American Museum Novitates, 2048, 1 - 42." type="journal article" year="1961">
Obraztsov (
<number box="[273,334,1129,1155]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1961.0">1961</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
both reported it only from the West Coast of North 
<collectingCountry box="[960,1065,1129,1155]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">America</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell" box="[1076,1243,1129,1155]" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Powell, J. A. (1964) Biological and taxonomic studies on tortricine moths, with reference to the species in California. University of California Publications in Entomology, 32, 317 pp." type="book" year="1964">
Powell (
<number box="[1174,1235,1129,1155]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that it is one of the most polyphagous species of North 
<collectingCountry box="[911,1012,1167,1193]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">America</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName box="[1019,1165,1167,1193]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="order">Lepidoptera</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1324,975,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<bibRefCitation author="Bondar" box="[312,484,1206,1232]" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Bondar, G. (1915) Insectos damninhos a agricultura, fasc. III. Plagas das laranjeiras e outras auranciaceae. Duprat &amp; Co., Sao Paulo, Brazil." type="book" year="1915">
Bondar (
<number box="[414,475,1206,1232]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1915.0">1915</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName box="[596,713,1206,1231]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Argyrotaenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrana">
<emphasis box="[596,713,1206,1231]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. citrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as attacking 
<taxonomicName box="[867,940,1206,1231]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rutaceae" genus="Citrus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[867,940,1206,1231]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Citrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[978,1053,1206,1232]" name="Brazil" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and this record probably was the source of subsequent citations of the species in South 
<collectingCountry box="[1077,1178,1244,1270]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">America</collectingCountry>
(e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Essig" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Essig, E. O. (1926) Insects of western North America. MacMillan Co., New York. 1035 pp." type="book" year="1926">
Essig 
<number box="[264,325,1282,1308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1926.0">1926</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ebeling" box="[338,501,1282,1308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Ebeling, W. (1959) Subtropical fruit pests. University of California Division of Agricultural Sciences. 436 pp." type="book" year="1959">
Ebeling 
<number box="[438,501,1282,1308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1959.0">1959</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Bondar" box="[645,817,1282,1308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Bondar, G. (1929) Insectos damninhos e molestias da laranjeiras no Brazil. Bolletin del Laboratorio Patologia y Vegetal, 7, 1 - 79." type="journal article" year="1929">
Bondar (
<number box="[748,809,1282,1308]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1929.0">1929</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
had reported this an error in identification (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell" box="[319,472,1321,1347]" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Powell, J. A. (1964) Biological and taxonomic studies on tortricine moths, with reference to the species in California. University of California Publications in Entomology, 32, 317 pp." type="book" year="1964">
Powell 
<number box="[409,472,1321,1347]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). It is likely that this species also was misidentified by Pastrana (
<emphasis box="[1242,1305,1321,1346]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">in litt</emphasis>
.) based on the previous literature, and we have no direct evidence that 
<taxonomicName box="[1088,1205,1360,1385]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Argyrotaenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrana">
<emphasis box="[1088,1205,1360,1385]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. citrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in 
<taxonomicName box="[264,385,1398,1424]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Argentina" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="7" pageNumber="9" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<collectingCountry box="[264,385,1398,1424]" name="Argentina" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Argentina</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1324,975,1616]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Based on evidence from mitochondrial 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" box="[779,843,1436,1462]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15536" name="Department of Natural Resources, Environment, The Arts and Sport" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">DNA</collectionCode>
and laboratory hybridization trials, 
<bibRefCitation pageId="7" pageNumber="9" refString="Landry, B., Powell, J. &amp; Sperling. F. (1999) Systematics of the Argyrotaenia franciscana (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) species group: Evidence from mitochondrial DNA. Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 92, 40 - 46." type="journal article">
Landry 
<emphasis box="[315,379,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[398,459,1474,1500]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1999.0">1999</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
concluded that 
<taxonomicName box="[668,790,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Argyrotaenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="citrana">
<emphasis box="[668,790,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. citrana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not clearly distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[1140,1315,1475,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Argyrotaenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franciscana">
<emphasis box="[1140,1315,1475,1500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. franciscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although they did not propose the synonymy of the two, their data strongly suggest that neither species is monophyletic relative the other. Hence the two may be considered more appropriately as synonyms, with 
<taxonomicName box="[652,823,1590,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Argyrotaenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="franciscana">
<emphasis box="[652,823,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">A. franciscana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the correct name based on priority.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
